      <title>Being A Proactive and Likable Engineer</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/career_reflection/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 15 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mycaptainmy@gmail.com (Yuan Meng)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/career_reflection/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;being-proactive-and-likable&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Being Proactive and Likable&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#being-proactive-and-likable&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;believe-in-yourself&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Believe In Yourself&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#believe-in-yourself&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;have a leap of faith&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;convince-others&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Convince Others&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#convince-others&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;argue with data, not intuitions or beliefs&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;help-efficiently&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Help Efficiently&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#help-efficiently&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;say no without using the word no &amp;mdash; make the trade offs clear&#xA;&amp;ldquo;showing that you are willing, and proving that you are busy&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Bounded Kindness (And Office Politics)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/awakening/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mycaptainmy@gmail.com (Yuan Meng)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/awakening/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I recently had 3 separate conversations with 3 colleagues I&amp;rsquo;m good friends with, all converging on the central theme of my 2024: &lt;strong&gt;awakening&lt;/strong&gt;. Two years into my career, I&amp;rsquo;m finally awakened to how office politics works, how I wish to play it, and what matters in my life.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;office-politics-no-such-things-as-deserving&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;strong&gt;Office Politics: No Such Things As &amp;ldquo;Deserving&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#office-politics-no-such-things-as-deserving&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;One colleague expressed indignation over a coasting, even toxic, tech lead getting the same level of recognition &amp;mdash; or at least compensation &amp;mdash; as another tech lead who worked tirelessly and selflessly mentored junior engineers (&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Why should he?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;). I chuckled inside: the world doesn&amp;rsquo;t operate on &amp;ldquo;shoulds&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;oughts&amp;rdquo;, but only on what is. There are no such things as &amp;ldquo;deserving&amp;rdquo; but only (1) aligning yourself with what your organization values and (2) getting rewarded for it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Seventeen Going Under</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/17_going_under/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 06 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mycaptainmy@gmail.com (Yuan Meng)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/17_going_under/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;See, I spent my teens enraged &lt;br/&gt; Spiralin&amp;rsquo; in silence &lt;br/&gt; And I armed myself with a grin &lt;br/&gt; &amp;lsquo;Cause I was always the fuckin&amp;rsquo; joker &lt;br/&gt; Buried in their humor &lt;br/&gt; Amongst the white noise &lt;br/&gt; &amp;mdash; Sam Fender, &lt;a href=&#34;https://open.spotify.com/track/5rF6YUIlgiat22OT1lWspJ?si=9a83e243ded34c2b&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Seventeen Going Under&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (2021)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When I was seventeen, it felt like the whole world was going to end. I was probably the only sexual minority in town that I knew of, and the headteacher asked that I stay home so the other kids could be rid of my &amp;ldquo;bad influence.&amp;rdquo; Also back then, never in a million years had I thought of one day turning my intellectual curiosity about what &amp;ldquo;learning&amp;rdquo; entails into a career (be it cognitive science or machine learning). Still, I fought for every opportunity that might yield some ambiguous reward someday, not knowing where it would lead â€” be it undergraduate research, graduate school applications, job interviews, or something &amp;ldquo;productive&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Brithday Wish</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/birthday/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 06 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mycaptainmy@gmail.com (Yuan Meng)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/birthday/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Survival was &lt;em&gt;the&lt;/em&gt; theme of this past year. When I expressed layoff worries in February 2022 (after Googling consequences of interest rate hikes as an econ noob&amp;hellip;), friends joked that I was a &amp;ldquo;Golden State Worrier&amp;rdquo;. After the chips were down last November, the shock was not one bit absorbed by anticipation. Seeing coworkers I just spoke and worked side by side with disappearing was unreal and painful. Since then I can&amp;rsquo;t quite recall the last time I felt truly exited or relaxed &amp;mdash; I seem to overdo what I can to feel a tiny bit safer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How Could Anyone Know How Another Feels?</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/empathy/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 09 Apr 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mycaptainmy@gmail.com (Yuan Meng)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/empathy/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The thought of my family&amp;rsquo;s graves &lt;br/&gt; Was the only moment &lt;br/&gt; I used to experience true love &lt;br/&gt; That love remains infinite &lt;br/&gt; As I&amp;rsquo;ll never be the man my father is &lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;How can you &amp;ldquo;just be yourself&amp;rdquo; &lt;br/&gt; When you don&amp;rsquo;t know who you are? &lt;br/&gt; Stop saying &amp;ldquo;I know how you feel&amp;rdquo; &lt;br/&gt; How could anyone know how another feels? &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&amp;mdash; Nightwish, &lt;em&gt;Song of Myself&lt;/em&gt; (2011)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Ph.D. Grind: Doing Nothing Is the Hardest Thing</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/notes/nothingness/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Mar 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>mycaptainmy@gmail.com (Yuan Meng)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/notes/nothingness/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;seriously-read-the-phd-grind&#34; class=&#34;scroll-mt-8 group&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Seriously, Read &lt;em&gt;The Ph.D. Grind&lt;/em&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;#seriously-read-the-phd-grind&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block&#34;&#xA;        aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to this heading&#34; tabindex=&#34;-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg&#xA;  xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&#xA;  width=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  height=&#34;16&#34;&#xA;  fill=&#34;none&#34;&#xA;  stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&#xA;  stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&#xA;  class=&#34;lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block&#34;&#xA;  viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Everyone doing a Ph.D. or considering doing one should read &lt;em&gt;The Ph.D. Grind&lt;/em&gt;. Don&amp;rsquo;t wait &amp;mdash; you&amp;rsquo;ll learn the much-needed &amp;ldquo;rational optimism&amp;rdquo; for this crazy ride.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
